reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very good tablet..
reviews.reviewText: This is a very nice tablet. A good blend of current hardware + software at this price point. It is Not slow, Not sluggish. Some things to speed it up (or any aAndroid device), don't enable auto account synh at setup, make sure auto synch off in accounts after set up, turn off play protect in Google play store, select do not auto update apps in Google play store. Comes with USB C cable not the charger. Has 2gb of Ram not 3gb, works at 2.4ghz wi-fi speed. Fast charging, about 2hrs from 0 to 100% charge. Full charge lasts about 4 to 6hrs. Android 12 /12S version loaded, able to load + run all new and old apps. 2gb of Ram, about 1gb always in use other 1gb relatively free to use. That said, don't want to have too many resource hungry apps open all at once: F'book, X, Tik, Netfl etc.. Great for gaming, e mail, movies, you tube, running all types of apps in general. Great gift or to update to newer hardware and latest Android version. Also with this and all Android be sure to clear the Chrome cache (any browser) both within the app as well as the Chrome (your browser) listed within the settings tab. Nice device for price. Enjoy!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Does not turn on after 2 weeks
reviews.reviewText: This is my first time buying something off Amazon since I'm only 11 but for an 11-year-old I know a lot you cannot play certain games on this tablet The games will be glitchy or it will literally say this product is not bound to have this app It stopped working and I blamed it on my mom but I took the back off of it to try and take the battery out and put it back in because that's what Google said would work and immediately when I took it off I seen that there were wires and tape that was extremely loose having the battery stick to the tablet one of the wires weren't even attached to the tablet battery which I'm guessing is why the tablet stopped working it doesn't even turn on anymore Another thing You can't really take good videos or good pictures Snapchat pictures are hard to take or just regular pictures in general And you can't even Set a timer for your pictures or videos You have to take a picture to see the picture that you already took and Is really irritating It froze time to time I still used it though Those two weeks were kind of fun Because I am homeschooled and I'm stuck in the house all day and also when I'm on Snapchat and I'm talking to my friends and they call me i can't hear anything if I join my group chat I can't hear anything they told me to put in headphones and that didn't even work i had to mute my mic to hear them which is really odd because it doesn't happen with any other tablet I get Or I don't think it happens Even though I literally only had Snapchat for one day because my mom made me delete it I could point out the things wrong with that tablet But I still used it cuz I was grateful.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 16, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Get ready to wait
reviews.reviewText: I bought this about a month ago and will stick with it for now, but boy this tablet proves you get what you pay for. First, it is beyond slow. My intent in getting this device was to use Evernote to read recipes in the kitchen. I just timed the device and from the time it is booted, it takes over 4 minutes to load a note in Evernote. Fortunately I can account for that and start early.But the other downer for this device is how weak the battery is. The same 4 minutes mentioned about used 9% of the battery, and that's in battery saver mode. I find that if I go 2 days without using this device, the battery will completely drain. Not sure what it's doing in the background, but I should probably monitor the traffic to see what's causing the drain.So if you need a super cheap device that has an easy interface and you're OK using it for non-dynamic apps and keeping it plugged in, this device is for you.
